# gitignore for Python, Java/Scala/Kotlin, C/C++, JavaScript/TypeScript, and Julia.
# This works well for many other languages, but it is NOT one-size-fits-all.
# It covers some common tools and IDEs, but it again isn't comprehensive.
# It also disregards obsolete files like Python `*.egg`.
#
# The approach is to blacklist `.*` and similar patterns, then to whitelist specific files.
# This approach makes the file much simpler and easier to understand.
# Some of the rules are derived from <https://github.com/github/gitignore/>.
#
# Whether to use a broad or tailored gitignore is debatable.
# I recommend a hybrid approach:
# - Tailor to per-repo languages, build tools, and runtime systems.
#   E.g. it's reasonable to remove the sqlite and Cmake sections.
# - Broadly cover popular IDEs and tools.
#   E.g. if vim starts prefixing temp files with `%`, you should probably add it.
#   Yes, developers should use `core.excludesfile`, but many don't.
# - Broadly ignore clearly unwanted files.
#   E.g. `aws-private-key.pem` should probably never be inside the repo,
#   but make sure it's ignored anyway.
# - Ignore dotfiles by default, then whitelist the ones you want.
#
# Notes:
# - Unlike  in `.dockerignore` and `.prettierignore`, patterns are relative.
#  `x` is equivalent to `**/x`, in contrast to `.dockerignore` and `.prettierignore`.
# - Always mark directories with a `/` suffix.
# - Per section, place directories above files; then sort lexicographically.
#   Order (using regex): `/` ≺ `*` ≺ `[^A-Za-z0-9]` ≺ `[0-9]` ≺ `[A-Za-z]`.
#   (Maybe eventually we'll have a Git hook do this.)

### Temporary paths ###

# Dotted paths (many whitelisted later)
.*

# Paths starting or ending in `~`, `$`, or `#`; or starting in `.~`.
# These are normally temp files like `~$doc.docx` or `.profile#`.
*[~#$]
[~#$]*
.~*

# Temp and misc. unwanted files
*[.~]bak
*[.~]out
*[.~]sw[opn]
*[.~]temp
*[.~]tmp
*.log
*.pid
*.pid.lock
Thumbs.db

### Large binary files ###

# Databases
*.sqlite3
*.sqlite3-journal

# Archives
*.7z
*.ear
*.gz
*.jar
*.lz4
*.lzma
*.tar
*.tar.gz
*.tgz
*.war
*.xz
*.zip
*.zst

# Executables and libraries
*.dll
*.dylib
*.exe
*.msi
*.pkg
*.so

# Credentials (best-effort)
credentials/
private/
secrets/
*.private
credentials.json
credentials.properties
credentials.yaml
secrets.json
secrets.properties
secrets.yaml

# Keystore/certificate files
*.asc
*.jks
*.key
*.keystore
*.pem
*.p12
*.pfx
*.pkcs12
id_rsa
id_ecdsa
id_ed25519

### Cross-language directories ###

# Build directories
/bin/
/build/
/dist/
/obj/
/out/
/sdist/
/target/

# Prebuilt libraries
/lib/
/vendor/

# Auto-generated docs
/docs/html/
/docs/_build/
/docs/autoapi/
/docs/generated/
/site/

### Language-specific paths ###

# Coverage
/coverage/
/htmlcov/

# Python
__pycache__/
__pypackages__/
cython_debug/
*.py[cod]
venv/

# Java
/pom.xml.*
*.class

# C and C++
*.a
*.pch
*.gch
*.ko
*.lib
*.lo
*.o
pch.h

### Temporary files for tools ###

# Make, CMake, automake, autoconf, pkg-config, etc.
_deps
*.la
*.pc
/cmake_install.cmake
/compile_commands.json
/install_manifest.txt

# JavaScript and TypeScript
node_modules/
tsconfig.tsbuildinfo
__snapshots__/

# Julia
*.jl.*.cov
*.jl.cov
*.jl.mem
deps/deps.jl

# Celery
celerybeat-schedule

# Terraform
override.tf
override.tf.json
*_override.tf
*_override.tf.json

### Whitelist specific dotfiles ###

# Git
!/.git-blame-ignore-revs
!/.gitattributes
!/.gitmodules

# GitHub
!/.devcontainer
!/.github/
!/.nojekyll

# AI tools
!/.claude/settings.json

# Linters
!/.editorconfig
!/.prettierrc*

### Whitelist general dotfile patterns ###

# Template env files
!/.env.template

# `.ignore` files (e.g. `.dockerignore`, `.npmignore`)
!/.*ignore

# Config files in the root
!/.*.jsonc
!/.*.toml
!/.*.yaml
!/.*.yml

# Config files in `.foo/*`
!/.*/[a-z0-9_-]*.jsonc
!/.*/[a-z0-9_-]*.toml
!/.*/[a-z0-9_-]*.yaml
!/.*/[a-z0-9_-]*.yml
